@hashimkhann._ dark matter is, as the name suggests, matter that is "dark" (a better term would be "invisible"). It's observed that galaxies behave as though there is extra mass present that cannot be seen or detected, hence dark matter has been inserted into the model.
@daddyodoug dark matter does not interact with light at all (except gravitationally, of course). So yes, light passes straight through it.
@arjun_jaya_prathap dark energy is present everywhere. It accounts for most of the mass-energy density of the universe.
